### Linux Permission String Structure

```
-rwxrw----
│├┤├┤├──┤
││ │ │  └─ Others: --- (no permissions)
││ │ └──── Group:  rw- (read + write)
││ └─────── Owner: rwx (read + write + execute)
│└───────── File type: - (regular file), d (directory)
```

### Octal Permission Reference

| Octal | Binary | Permissions | Meaning |
|-------|--------|-------------|---------|
| `7` | `111` | `rwx` | Read + Write + Execute |
| `6` | `110` | `rw-` | Read + Write |
| `5` | `101` | `r-x` | Read + Execute |
| `4` | `100` | `r--` | Read only |
| `0` | `000` | `---` | No permissions |

### Symbolic Mode Reference

| Syntax | Meaning |
|--------|---------|
| `u+w` | Add write permission for owner (user) |
| `g-x` | Remove execute for group |
| `o-r` | Remove read for others |
| `a+r` | Add read for all (user, group, others) |

